< Review>
The entrance and parking to this place is in the back alley-like street it shares with Urban Ore, through two garage door entrances.

They have two main rooms of wood, one of hardwood boards and one just of veneered plywood. You are free to look though and pick out exactly what you want, board by board. They are not at all pushy, you get lots of hobbiest folks through here.

Once you have the desired boards, ask them to write up the boards. They'll make a slip, which you take inside to pay, leave the wood while you pay. Come back out and take your wood!

Love this place. Good prices and nice people.</Review>

<review>Looking for long pieces of wood to build a tabletop and macbeath made me feel very welcome. I love being able to sift through inventory and pick out what I need. I was able to find a few 9 ft long maple planks and matching legs. Come ready to do some lifting. Parking is a free for all but when you're ready to load your car they let u drive it into the warehouse.

As a beginner a few things to know about this location specifically. They cant rip boards on site meaning if you want to change a 10inch wide board into 8 inches they have to send it out to their HQ which will take a week. Their boards were misc widths, I found 8 9 and 10 inch boards up to 12 ft long. They can (cross) cut them to 9 ft long for you but I had to buy the extra 2-3 ft amounts and it is a rough cut not a perfect 90 degree cut</review><Pictures>None<//Pictures>< response>

I called on 5/30/2019 @ 9:32am for a quote to do a Smog test on my 1999 Honda Civic EX  and was given a quote of $48 out of the door. When I came to this place at 12:10 pm, guy came out to me, looked at my car and said it will be $96 to smog may car, even though I told him that I called and got a different quote. I was really confused, so I called that same number again and talked to the very polite and helpful woman on the phone which said to give the Tech guy last 4 digits of my phone number. After talking to the Tech again, this time he decided that he can not smog my car because it was "too low", even though my car has stock suspension and has bigger than original wheels which overall makes it slightly higher than stock. Two minutes later Tech's buddy showed up to do a smog on his car, they started chatting, and completely ignoring me. After talking to the same helpful woman on the phone she told me that I can go to a different Horizon Smog place on El Camino to do my Smog (which had the same ramp and my car did not have an issue getting on it).

So if you want shady people like this guy to do anything on your car come to this place. Or if you simply want to get ripped off.</review>

<Rating>1<//Rating>< Text>
They make rather deceptive claims. In the quote for the original test, it says: "FREE RE-TEST FOR VEHICLES THAT FAIL THE INITIAL SMOG CHECK VALID UNTIL 90 DAYS AFTER THE INITIAL TEST." My car failed the original test because the battery had recently died and the monitors had not run through all their internal checks. I returned 21 days after the initial test and was charged $21.75 for the retest (plus $8.25 for the certificate, as expected).

When I challenged the quote, I was told "yes, you get one free chance for a retest, so it is only $30 instead of $48." That was repeated multiple times as I tried to understand how "free" was turning into "$21.75" until I was told that the re-test was free, but I still had to pay for the labor, as "he had to do the whole test again." Perhaps he did, but new customers showed up shortly thereafter and my re-test took about 5 minutes compared to the 15-20 for the first one, and there is no difference in the line-items on the receipts to show that one included charges for something that was at all "free" the second time.</Text>

< review>
This place is the worst smog shop I've ever seen or been to. They failed the car do to no under hood sticker. Witch wasn't that bad. There is a free retest. I came back for the second test with under hood sticker. Now they failed it for a weld on the cat. Both cats are welded from the factory. Even if the cat was welded. It would be considered a repair. Not missing or modified. I know this because I am a Master ASE with my Advanced level L1. Certified on Mazda and Subaru. I also had my smog license from 1990 to 2012.
It gets worse. During the first test the guy pinched one of his tools between the hood and the windshield, cracking the windshield. They would not repair it. Basically told me to go bound sand.
The car had passed at the Referee station with the same cat and no under hood sticker last time. I guess these guy's follow different rules than anyone else I know.

RESPONSE FROM CUSTOMER

I agree the technician made the correct decision. Witch was check for the under hood emission label, and if not there. He goes to the book. The statement "We can't smog a vehicle with out no emission label." is completely incorrect. You should not give out false information to the public.
I did bring the car back for a free retest with the emissions label. The smog technician did worked on the vehicle with out authorization. Witch is a BAR violation.  Your technician failed the vehicle for a completely different reason the second time. Star was started by the BAR so things would be consistent in the smog program. Witch you clearly proved that your not.

Susanne Bj√∂rnson</user_name>
<Date>1621904022832<//Date><rating>5</rating>< text>
Before meeting Dr Rogers I was only aware of one surgery for stress urinary incontinence, and that was a sling . I did not believe that was a good  choice for me, as I felt the recovery was quiet long, and the possibility of something going wrong down the line could happen, as
with all surgeries...There was also the dreaded pad!
Dr Rogers introduced me to a procedure called Bulkamid, it‚Äôs a gel like substance(97.5% water, 2.5% polyacrylamide) that is placed on your urethral wall to ‚Äúbulk up‚Äù, hence no more embarrassing leaking, when sneezing, coughing , jumping or running.You are put under sedation by her great team in the OR, the procedure probably only takes 30 minutes, and you are out of Sansum Surgery Center in less than 3 hours. I highly recommend this procedure to all women with the same issues as I had!
Dr Rogers is super easy to communicate with, she made me feel comfortable ,talking about something uncomfortable and slighty embarrassing (to me)
And her choice of sneakers is always on trendü§©

Sincerely,
Susanne Bj√∂rnson< /text>

<review>We have pets. Currently, two cats and an old dog. Thank goodness our pets are pretty healthy, but every once in a while we need a vet and Nipomo Dog and Cat Hospital is the best we've found. Every one of the doctors we've had the pleasure of working with has been great. We always leave feeling like we've been a part of the process, listened to and informed. We recently lost our old gray cat named, Gray Kitty. The doctor couldn't have been more compassionate, helpful or informative. This is a hard thing for people but the focus was on what was best for the animal. With great sadness we left Gray at the vet but we were very grateful and knew she was being treated with respect. A few days later we received a card with the office's condolences and a paw print from Gray. A couple of years ago we had the dog in. She was off her feed and lethargic. The doctor explained what she thought the problem was. She could order expensive tests or go straight to treatment. If the dog responded to treatment it would be diagnostic and we would avoid paying the high cost of testing, or worse, deciding we couldn't afford the tests. This solved the problem and Maggie is older now but still a happy dog thanks to Dr. Stamp. We are fortunate to have such a great vet clinic in NIpomo.

Update:
Maggie the old Lab finally reached the point she was not enjoying her time here. We contacted Nipomo Dog and Cat Hospital to see how we could go about making arrangements for Maggie. Everyone we spoke to was great. When we brought her in the staff was as supportive as anyone could be. They explained the process and asked us how we wanted to arrange things. It was as peaceful as it could be and staff made sure we had as much time as we needed. It's a tough thing but the people at this vet made it as easy as it could be. Maggie is now happy in the place where the ducks always fly.<//review><Pics>None<//Pics>< Response>

Nipomo Dog and Cat Hospital is truly the very best of the best.  Everyone in the facility from outstanding doctors to caring, skillful vet techs treats my pets as if they were their own.  Their compassion and willingness to go the extra mile to ensure a pet's well-being is beyond outstanding.  In 60 years of working with veterinarians, I have never found a vet hospital with this uniform level of excellence.  With multiple pets, I deeply appreciate their skill, experience and integrity in providing and explaining all treatment options without pressure to delve into costly areas that may cause the pet unnecessary distress with little productivity. <rating>5< /rating>< review>
Nipomo Dog and Cat Hospital is so much more than just another veterinary clinic! From the moment you walk through the front door you are greeted by a friendly yet professional staff who will get you checked in and questions answered. All the doctors and veterinary techs and assistants are wonderful...they are compassionate, skilled, and often use a team-approach to determine appropriate treatment. Options are presented, being mindful of what is best for your pet and for you! They listen!
We even have friends that drive down from San Luis Obispo to have their animals seen and treated at Nipomo Dog and Cat Hospital!
We adopted our two kitties, Lenny and Francis through their animal rescue non-profit, Animals in Need, thanks to a phone call from Dr. Stamp. She knew we were planning to adopt and kept us in mind when the boys were dropped off (and never picked up) from a free spay and neuter event.
We cannot recommend Nipomo Dog and Cat highly enough!!!

Karen and Jack Carson</review>

This place is a beacon of excellent veterinary care, especially along the Central Coast, where vets are many, yet integrity, service and just plain caring warmth towards our pets is hard to find.  The office staff is efficient and friendly, and the veterinary staff, doctors, techs and assistants are  seemingly bound by a singular mission of top notch service. THIS is the place!

One might suppose that my initial great experiences with NDCH might have been accidental.  Not so!  In the 3 years we have been up here on the Central Coast, NDCH has been consistently excellent, even on their busiest days, which leads me to believe, based on personal experience, that excellence IS the norm. <time>1488490394029<//time><rate>5</rate>< text>
The professionals at Nipomo Dog & Cat Hospital are absolutely amazing!  We have been taking our pets to Dr.s Robyn and Maggie for close to 20 years and followed them as they set up this practice.  We travel 20 minutes each way to take our pets here.

Let me give you an example of the love every single person here provides to their fur patients and owners:

About 3 1/2 years ago we adopted a dog from our local humane society.  At her well-doggie check-up, a huge mass was discovered.  Not only did the compassionate Dr.s and techs provide AMAZING care of my dog, they supported us in working with the humane society in contributing to the cost of the surgery.

Most importantly, when it was decided that Sierra needed an overnight stay, her Dr. took Sierra to her home and administered pain medication throughout the night.  Who does that?

When time came for Sierra to cross over the rainbow bridge, our Dr. cried as she told us the news and made a contribution to the Veterinary Research Center at UC Davis in Sierra's name.

I honestly feel that the professionals here treat my pet as if it was their own...what more can I ask for?  Unbelievable people, each and every one!<//text>

<rating>5</rating><Text>Doctors Maggie Wagner and Robin Shroyer have cared for my animals since I moved to the Central Coast from Oregon in 2001.

When they opened their present facility quite a few years ago, my pets continued to recieve the same outstanding care by the new veterinarians, techs and support staff hired as their practice continued to thrive and grow.

Every veterinarian hired by Drs. Wagner and Shroyer is just as professional, knowledgeable and personable as they themselves are. I don't know how long or where they they look, but they find great ones!

Each doctor really takes the time to get to know your pet, asks and answers  questions, listens to you and discusses multiple treatment options. And unneeded procedures, pills, shots and special food isn't pushed on your pet just to inflate your bill, like some offices may do.

When I had an ill cat, these doctors wouldn't give up until they figured out what was wrong with him. They spent hours researching, conferred long distance with their peers, and went over and above what was expected to find what was causing his illness‚Äîand against all odds, they did find his very rare disease, and a treatment for it.

All in all, I highly recommend Nipomo Dog and Cat Hospital. It is an extremely clean, well-run, professional office.< /Text>< pictures>

< Review>
Great food, reasonable prices especially for lunch. For slightly more than fast food pricing you get a sit down lunch. One of the few places (even counting expensive steak places) that serves you complimemtary freshly baked bread while you wait for your entrees. I visited today after years of ignoring it as a lunch choice, but this visit has certainly put Olive Garden on my go to list from now on.</Review>

<username>Brent Sanchez< /username><date>1490056906687<//date>< Rating>
3</Rating>
< Review>
**Update**
This Olive Garden has been remodeled and looks absolutely gorgeous. However... it has gone in a different direction in other ways. They replaced the cloth napkins for paper ones. In my opinion the cloth napkins gave Olive Garden a small essence of a higher class establishment and now it's just another pasta place. The face-lift would have bumped my rating to a 4 but it will stay at 3 bc of the downgrade in the smaller areas.

You can pass this Olive Garden if you do not know where to turn in but the food is always great. This Olive Garden has always had excellent wait staff. Only gets 3 stars because there have been times where wait time for the food has gone a bit long, even when the house isnt packed.</Review>
